1
00:00:02,917 --> 00:00:06,047
Once someone was trying 
to say that and explain,

2
00:00:06,047 --> 00:00:11,967
when Gaudiya Math 
was accused of promoting slavery,

3
00:00:12,221 --> 00:00:14,831
[Dignity of the Human Race]

4
00:00:15,503 --> 00:00:23,043
saying, “What is Kṛṣṇa das and dāsī—
‘slave girl’, ‘slave’, all slave?”

5
00:00:23,043 --> 00:00:27,918
And not even directly the slave, 
but slave of the slave.

6
00:00:27,918 --> 00:00:29,060
[Laughing]

7
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:31,542
So the British say, 
“And we are humanists,

8
00:00:31,542 --> 00:00:39,952
we tried to eliminate 
this sort of idea

9
00:00:40,132 --> 00:00:46,002
hundreds of years ago 
with the introduction of humanism.”

10
00:00:46,199 --> 00:00:48,449
But Saraswati Ṭhākur’s response,
he said,

11
00:00:48,469 --> 00:00:53,714
“No, Gaudiya Math stands
for the dignity of the human race.

12
00:00:53,714 --> 00:00:56,370
To be the slave of Kṛṣṇa,

13
00:00:56,370 --> 00:00:59,530
the servant of Kṛṣṇa, 
that is not a low position.

14
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:02,420
That is a very high position.”

15
00:01:02,498 --> 00:01:04,528
But sometimes 
people shy away from that word.

16
00:01:04,528 --> 00:01:06,896
They think,
“Servant has a nicer ring to it.”

17
00:01:06,958 --> 00:01:11,362
Or they try and act 
as apologists saying,

18
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:13,442
“No, that’s not what 
he was saying.”

19
00:01:13,442 --> 00:01:15,362
No, it is what he was saying.

20
00:01:15,426 --> 00:01:21,466
I can show you 108 references
in the talks of Srīla Guru Mahārāj,

21
00:01:21,466 --> 00:01:26,236
where he is using the word ‘slave’:
“Happy dancing slaves of Kṛṣṇa”,

22
00:01:26,236 --> 00:01:28,746
“We are meant 
to be the slaves of Kṛṣṇa”,

23
00:01:28,746 --> 00:01:32,146
“Slavery is the only position 
to approach Him”.

24
00:01:32,146 --> 00:01:36,003
So then we all 
get nervous and worried,

25
00:01:36,003 --> 00:01:39,243
and think, 
“Who can we tell this to?”

26
00:01:39,243 --> 00:01:42,243
But we need to hear 
the full picture.

27
00:01:42,246 --> 00:01:46,626
ye yathā māṁ prapadyante 
taṁs tathaiva bhajāmy aham 
[Bg: 4.11]

28
00:01:46,728 --> 00:01:52,648
This is why no less a word 
than slavery can be used.

29
00:01:52,648 --> 00:01:54,488
That sort of giving over;

30
00:01:54,488 --> 00:01:58,688
Rūpa Goswāmī quotes Jīva [Goswāmī] 
saying, “Like a sold animal.”

31
00:01:58,688 --> 00:02:02,380
Like when Gurudev 
offered himself to Guru Mahārāj

32
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:05,380
and said, “I’m your goat,

33
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:10,760
if it pleases you to cut off my tail, 
you can do that.

34
00:02:10,811 --> 00:02:13,337
Or you can slit my throat—
I’m your goat, 
 

35
00:02:13,337 --> 00:02:16,337
whatever you want 
you can do with me.”

36
00:02:16,337 --> 00:02:22,897
It’s not that conditionally ‘I am yours’;
unconditionally ‘I am yours’.

37
00:02:22,956 --> 00:02:25,296
Why is this so important?

38
00:02:25,296 --> 00:02:32,236
Because Kṛṣṇa is reciprocating
the devotion of the devotee.

39
00:02:32,237 --> 00:02:36,787
So for those who offer themselves 
as slaves to Kṛṣṇa,

40
00:02:36,787 --> 00:02:39,926
Kṛṣṇa becomes their slave.

41
00:02:40,032 --> 00:02:41,822
That’s what 
He reciprocates with them.

42
00:02:41,822 --> 00:02:47,982
That’s how bound He is by the love 
and affection of the devotees.

43
00:02:47,982 --> 00:02:51,829
So when the ladies, 
the elderly gopīs in Vrindavan,

44
00:02:51,834 --> 00:02:57,394
they tell Kṛṣṇa, “Dance, Gopāl, dance!
We want to see your dance.”

45
00:02:57,439 --> 00:03:01,319
He starts dancing 
to make them happy.

46
00:03:01,363 --> 00:03:05,233
“Gopāl, hand me that!”

47
00:03:05,515 --> 00:03:08,927
Sometimes He can … and then 
He goes and brings them thing.

48
00:03:08,927 --> 00:03:13,857
But sometimes they ask Him 
to pick up something that’s too heavy.

49
00:03:13,857 --> 00:03:17,436
So He just touches it, like that.

50
00:03:17,511 --> 00:03:20,331
But sometimes He is showing,
“I am very strong”.

51
00:03:20,394 --> 00:03:23,248
He is omnipotent, 
the Supreme Reality,

52
00:03:23,248 --> 00:03:27,398
but He is a plaything
in the hands of the Vraja-gopīs.

53
00:03:27,467 --> 00:03:31,987
They make Him dance, sing 
and play in different ways.

54
00:03:31,988 --> 00:03:36,288
And happily He is their plaything,
their puppet.

55
00:03:36,301 --> 00:03:41,441
So for those who offer themselves 
as slave, abject slavery to Kṛṣṇa,

56
00:03:41,441 --> 00:03:44,833
He reciprocates 
by becoming their slave.

57
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:50,819
We give half-hearted approach—
half-hearted response.

58
00:03:50,819 --> 00:03:54,729
But, so what would be the most intense 
way you could offer yourself?

59
00:03:54,729 --> 00:03:57,468
—Slave.
That’s the operative word.

60
00:03:57,468 --> 00:04:00,276
And Guru Mahārāj said, 
“And not even directly slave—

61
00:04:00,276 --> 00:04:01,676
[Laughing]

62
00:04:01,711 --> 00:04:05,786
slave of the slave of the slave”—
dāsa-dāsānudāsaḥ

63
00:04:05,786 --> 00:04:08,263
gopī-bhartuḥ pada-kamalayor

64
00:04:08,263 --> 00:04:10,043
dāsa-dāsānudāsaḥ 
[Cc: 2.13.80]

